# Backend deploy via `ekatraa_backend_recovery_push`

This repo’s **`origin/main`** may lag your daily checkout. The sibling repo **`ekatraa_backend_recovery_push`** tracks GitHub (`ekatraa2025-git/ekatraa-backend`) and is used for commits/pushes.

## Workflow

1. Finish edits here (`ekatraa_backend`).
2. Copy changed paths into **`../ekatraa_backend_recovery_push`** so layouts stay aligned (`src/`, `migrations/`, etc.).
3. In **`ekatraa_backend_recovery_push`**: `git status`, stage intentionally, **`git commit`** with a clear message, **`git push origin main`**.
4. Do not force-push or rewrite remote history unless the team explicitly asks.

## Tips

- Run ESLint on touched TS route/lib files before commit when feasible.
- If Supabase migrations changed here, mirror them into recovery_push before push.
